        <abstract> 
<p>Encloses advertisement [for C. R. Bree, <hi rend="italic">Species not transmutable</hi> (1860)].</p> 
            <p>Discusses Bronn’s chapter of criticisms.</p>
            <p>Mentions variation in rats.</p>
            <p>Has ordered book by Bree.</p>
            <p>Discusses suggestion that southern corners of Australia may once have been islands.</p>
            <p>Mentions "wild speculations" about change in earth’s axes.</p>
            <p>CL’s ideas on variation.</p>
        </abstract>
